{"id":1274740836,"question_id":3445,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 week, 3 days","timestamp":1717297393,"status":11,"status_display":"Wrong Answer","runtime":"N/A","url":"/submissions/detail/1274740836/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Lexicographically Minimum String After Removing Stars","memory":"N/A","code":"class Solution {\n    public String clearStars(String s) {\n        int del = 0;\n        \n        for(char ch : s.toCharArray()){\n            if(ch=='*') del++;\n        }\n        \n        if(del==0) return s;\n        \n        TreeMap<Character, Integer> map = new TreeMap<>();\n        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++){\n            char ch = s.charAt(i);\n            if(ch=='*'){\n                char f = map.firstKey();\n                map.put(f, map.get(f)-1 );\n                if(map.get(f)==0) map.remove(f);\n                \n            }else{\n                map.put(ch, map.getOrDefault(ch,0)+1);\n            }\n            \n        }\n        \n        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\n        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++){\n            char ch = s.charAt(i);\n            if(map.containsKey(ch)){\n                sb.append(ch);\n                \n                map.put(ch, map.get(ch)-1);\n                if(map.get(ch)==0) map.remove(ch);\n            }\n            \n            \n        }\n        \n        return sb.toString();\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"lexicographically-minimum-string-after-removing-stars","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
